                            <comment id="14615529" author="alexiswilke" created="Mon, 6 Jul 2015 19:55:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For sure my loop was wrong. We would need to start at size - 1. Which ever way it is written would be more secure than not clearing the password buffer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;for(int i(userPassword.size() - 1); i &amp;gt;= 0; --i)
{
    userPassword[i] = &apos;*&apos;;
} 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
